# ============================================
# MONGODB CONFIGURATION
# ============================================
#
# MongoDB is used for flexible metadata storage in the hybrid booking system:
# - Booking metadata (custom fields per studio type)
# - Form schemas (dynamic booking forms)
# - Form responses (customer-submitted data)
# - Booking notes & attachments
# - Cancellation reasons & refund notes
#
# Core booking data remains in Neon PostgreSQL for ACID compliance.
#
# ============================================

# MongoDB Connection String
# Get from: MongoDB Atlas → Your Cluster → Connect → Connect your application
# Format: mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority
# IMPORTANT: Use MongoDB Atlas for serverless/edge deployments
VITE_MONGODB_CONNECTION_STRING=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# MongoDB Database Name
# The name of the database to use in MongoDB
VITE_MONGODB_DB_NAME=seshnx

# ============================================
# Setup Instructions
# ============================================
#
# 1. Create MongoDB Atlas account (https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas)
# 2. Create a new cluster (free tier available for development)
# 3. Create a database user (username + password)
# 4. Whitelist your IP address (or use 0.0.0.0/0 for Vercel)
# 5. Get connection string from Atlas → Connect → Connect your application
# 6. Copy connection string to VITE_MONGODB_CONNECTION_STRING above
#
# ============================================
# Security Best Practices
# ============================================
#
# ✅ DO:
# - Use strong passwords for database users
# - Enable IP whitelisting in MongoDB Atlas
# - Enable TLS/SSL for connections
# - Use Atlas Search for text queries (not regex on large datasets)
# - Monitor MongoDB Atlas logs for suspicious activity
#
# ❌ DON'T:
# - Commit MongoDB credentials to version control
# - Share credentials via email/chat
# - Use production database in development
# - Disable authentication in production
#
# ============================================
# Hybrid Architecture
# ============================================
#
# Neon (PostgreSQL) - Core Data:
# - bookings (transactional records)
# - payments (financial data)
# - booking_status_history (audit trail)
# - users, profiles (authentication data)
#
# MongoDB - Flexible Data:
# - booking_metadata (studio-specific requirements)
# - form_schemas (dynamic form definitions)
# - form_responses (customer submissions)
# - booking_notes (flexible notes)
# - booking_attachments (file metadata)
#
# Why Hybrid?
# ✅ Financial safety with ACID guarantees (Neon)
# ✅ Unlimited flexibility without migrations (MongoDB)
# ✅ Audit trail for compliance (Neon)
# ✅ Zero-downtime schema changes (MongoDB)
#
# ============================================
